This paper is about automatic evaluation of dialogue responses, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also presents a learning model for dialogue evaluation, which falls under machine learning (ML) and specifically, deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of having an accurate automatic evaluation procedure for dialogue research, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and user studies. Therefore, cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) are also possible sub-categories.
